6.42	First-past-the-post_election_system	First-past-the-post voting	First-past-the-post (abbreviated FPTP or FPP) voting refers to an election won by the candidate(s) with the most votes. The winning candidate does not necessarily receive an absolute majority of all votes cast.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/ee/Percentage_graph_UK_POLITICS_2005.png/220px-Percentage_graph_UK_POLITICS_2005.png
